  86:6:4:"The fourth word of verse (86:6) is an indefinite masculine active participle and is in the genitive case (<span class=\"at\">مجرور</span>). The active participle's triliteral root is <i class=\"ab\">dāl fā qāf</i> (<span class=\"at\">د ف ق</span>)."
  86:7:1:"The first word of verse (86:7) is an imperfect verb (<span class=\"at\">فعل مضارع</span>). The verb is third person masculine singular and is in the indicative mood (<span class=\"at\">مرفوع</span>). The verb's triliteral root is <i class=\"ab\">khā rā jīm</i> (<span class=\"at\">خ ر ج</span>)."
  86:7:2:"The second word of verse (86:7) is a preposition."
