  86:8:3:"The third word of verse (86:8) is divided into 2 morphological segments. A noun and possessive pronoun. The noun is masculine and is in the genitive case (<span class=\"at\">مجرور</span>). The noun's triliteral root is <i class=\"ab\">rā jīm ʿayn</i> (<span class=\"at\">ر ج ع</span>). The attached possessive pronoun is third person masculine singular."
