  86:9:1:"The first word of verse (86:9) is a masculine time adverb and is in the accusative case (<span class=\"at\">منصوب</span>). The time adverb's triliteral root is <i class=\"ab\">yā wāw mīm</i> (<span class=\"at\">ي و م</span>)."
  86:9:2:"The second word of verse (86:9) is a passive imperfect verb (<span class=\"at\">فعل مضارع</span>). The verb is third person feminine singular and is in the indicative mood (<span class=\"at\">مرفوع</span>). The verb's triliteral root is <i class=\"ab\">bā lām wāw</i> (<span class=\"at\">ب ل و</span>)."
  86:9:3:"The third word of verse (86:9) is a feminine plural noun and is in the nominative case (<span class=\"at\">مرفوع</span>). The noun's triliteral root is <i class=\"ab\">sīn rā rā</i> (<span class=\"at\">س ر ر</span>)."
